{[#]} 28. Bxf6 $1 {White crushes the position of the opponent's king.} gxf6 29.
Qe7 $1 {with a double threat – to take on d8 and to checkmate with Rg3.} Qxb3
$8 30. Qxd8+ Kf7 31. Qc7+ $1 {An important intermediate check.} Kg6 32. Qxc8
Qe3+ 33. Kh1 Ra7 {The forcing line has ended; it is time to evaluate the
position. The black king is weak; pawn d5 can become dangerous; White wins.
The possible continuation is} 34. Qg4+ Kf7 35. h3 $18 *

