[SourceQuality "1"]

{Pawn sacrifices The following three games involve an element of preparation
as in each of them, white sacrificed a pawn to establish the bishop on the
a2-g8 diagonal. Isaak Boleslavsky decided to help his light-squared bishop to
reach the a2-g8 diagonal.} 24. a4 $1 ({A quiet try to reach the a2-g8 diagonal
would not work:} 24. bxa5 Qxa5 25. Bd1 Nc5 $1 {with an equal play.}) 24... bxa4
25. b5 {Black's extra pawn does not play a serious role. Control over the
light squares means much more. With a B on c4, White is a side fighting for a
win. Olof Sterner was doing well for quite a long but finally made a serious
mistake.} Qd7 26. Rfc1 Rfc8 27. Bc4 $1 Nc5 28. Rxc8+ Rxc8 29. Qa2 Bf6 30. Rb1
$6 Rb8 $2 (30... Bc3 $1 {followed by Bb4 was stronger. After missing this
chance, Black finds himself in a practically lost position.}) 31. Qd2 Qc7 32.
Qd5 Rb6 $2 (32... a3 $1 {with an idea of Bb2 was stronger (again Black might
restrict the opponent's rook).}) 33. Qa8+ (33. Rd1 $1 {with an idea of e4-e5!
was already winning.}) 33... Rb8 34. b6 Qb7 {[#] One more interesting
calculating exercise. How should White play?} 35. Qxa5 ({The best move was} 35.
Qa7 $1 {Black should lose time to prevent the Bd5 idea.} Ra8 (35... Qxa7 $2 36.
bxa7 Rxb1+ 37. Kf2 $18) 36. Qxb7 Nxb7 37. Bd5 Rb8 38. f4 $1 $18 {to have e4-e5
in the case of Nc5. Black pieces are paralyzed.}) 35... Bd8 36. Bxc5 dxc5 37.
Qxa4 Bxb6 38. Rd1 $16 {[#] Black has managed to save the material balance up
to now but the position remained difficult. White has a free pawn on the
kingside and strong pressure on the f7-pawn.} Bc7 39. Qd7 Rf8 40. e5 $1 {
It is impossible to win the game without the kingside pawns.} Qb6 41. f4 Qb8
42. h4 $1 Ba5 43. h5 Bc3 {[#]} 44. Rd6 $1 {White left the king undefended but
Black has no time to create serious threats because of Qxf7 motive.} Qb1+ 45.
Kh2 h6 (45... Qe1 46. Qxf7+ Rxf7 47. Rd8#) 46. Qxf7+ $1 {The queen sacrifice
can decorate any game.} Rxf7 47. Rd8+ Kh7 48. Bxf7 ({Black resigned because of
material losses.} 48. Bxf7 g5 49. hxg6+ Qxg6 (49... Kg7 50. Rg8#) 50. Bxg6+ $18
) 1-0

