{[#] White can take the pawn with a check, but we should never forget that
pawns in the middlegames with opposite-colored bishops do not matter much.
White increases the number of attacking soldiers.} 44. h5 $1 {White has two
ideas – to play h5-h6 with an idea of Qg7# or to exchange on g6 to open the
h-file. Both threats are mating. Black has no defense.} ({Old analysis of this
game stated that White wins with} 44. f5 $2 Rd8 45. Qxe6+ Kg7 46. Qe7+ Kh6 47.
Qg5+ Kg7 48. Re1 Re8 49. Re7+ {and so on.}) ({But in fact, move} 44. f5 {
loses all advantage to tricky} Kh8 $1 {with Rd8 idea.}) 44... Bxf4 45. hxg6
hxg6 46. Qxe6+ Kh8 47. Qh3+ Kg7 48. Rd7+ Kf6 49. Qe6+ Kg5 50. Qe7+ $1 Rf6 (
50... Kg4 51. Be2+ Kg3 (51... Kf5 52. g4#) 52. Rd3+ $18) 51. Rd5+ $18 *

