{[#]} 23... fxg4 {The first move is forced.} 24. fxe5 Nf5 {Again no choice for
Black. But what to do after} 25. exd6 {?} Qxd6 $3 ({Nidjat Mamedov correctly
recognized the combination motive but failed to find the correct move order  
(to be honest, I even have not seen a motive).} 25... Qd8 $1 26. Bxb6 $4 ({
My reaction proved that I saw nothing special for Black. Otherwise, I would
probably find the distracting move} 26. d7 $1 {It reminds me of the a6-a7
advancing in the main lines of my favorite Benko gambit.} Rxc4 $1 {The
necessary move.} ({The primitive captures leave White the advantageous
position:} 26... Bxe3+ $2 27. Rxe3 Qxd7 28. Re6) 27. Qxf5 $1 {This is the
point!} Rxf5 28. Bxc4 $13 {and White is probably fine.}) 26... Qxb6+ 27. c5 {
White has a nice mass of pawns and it looks so that Black miscalculated
something. But here, my opponent shocked me with} Rxc5 $3 28. bxc5 Qxc5+ 29.
Kh1 Qf2 $1 {[#] The combination came to its end. White pieces are unable to
defend their king. I have found the only practical chance which surprisingly
worked well.} 30. Re4 $1 Qh4+ $2 ({The correct way was} 30... Ng3+ $1 31. Kh2
Rf5 32. Re8+ Kf7 $19 {and it's time to resign.}) 31. Qh3 $1 {A nice move that
allowed me to escape the instant resignation.} Ng3+ 32. Kg1 Qxh3 33. gxh3 Nxe4
$17) 26. c5 Rxc5 $3 {Black cleans up the a7-g1 diagonal.} 27. bxc5 Bxc5 28.
Rac1 ({After} 28. Bxc5 Qxc5+ 29. Kh1 Qf2 $19 {we see the game position without
the White pawn on d6.}) 28... Nxe3 29. Rxe3 ({One more important nuance of the
combination is hidden in the following line:} 29. Rxc5 Nxf1 $1 {A threat of 
checkmate on h2 forces White to take on f1.} 30. Rxf1 Qxc5+ 31. Kh2 Rxf1 32.
Qxf1 Qxd5 $19) 29... Ba7 $1 {Black avoids Rxc5. [#] Again, we see a position
with a free rook for White,, the best he has now is the worst endgame.} 30. Kh1
$1 (30. Rce1 $2 Qg3 $1 31. Qc3 Re8 $19) 30... Qf4 31. g3 Qxe3 32. Qxe3 Bxe3 {
it is hard to say if Black is already technically winning with two free pawns
but a long fight waits for White.} *

