{There are times when the White dark-squared bishop can dominate the h4-d8
diagonal.} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ne7 7. h4
{The ideas of this move are to advance the pawn to h6 (if allowed) to weaken
the dark squares on the kingside and to free the path to develop the rook (via
h3 or even h4).} Qa5 8. Bd2 Nbc6 9. Rb1 b6 {[#]} 10. Bb5 $1 {White threatens
to win the material with a move c3-c4; that's why the next Black's move looks
logical.} c4 ({Though, the engine says that a capture of the pawn is possible.
} 10... Qxa3 11. Ne2 $1 {(getting ready to attack the queen on a2 from c1)} (
11. Rb3 Qa5 $1 (11... Qa2 $4 12. Qc1 $1 {followed by Ra3.}) 12. c4 Qa2) 11...
a6 12. Rb3 axb5 $5 13. Rxa3 Rxa3 $16) {After move c5-c4 Black bishop is
restricted and White begins the operation of weakening the dark squares.} 11.
Qg4 Rg8 12. Bxc6+ Nxc6 13. h5 h6 {Naturally, Black is not ready to allow the
h5-h6 move.} 14. Ne2 Ne7 15. Qh4 $2 ({Both opponents were under the impression
that Black neven can take on a3. For this reason, a few next moves will be
marked with "?". After the engine's move} 15. Ra1 $5 {White can cope with the
Black's active attempts on the queenside.} Bd7 (15... Qb5 16. Be3 Qb2 17. Kd2)
(15... Qa4 16. Kd1) 16. a4 $1 {A typical sacrifice.} Bxa4 17. Bc1 b5 18. Kd2
$16 {and then Ba3 with a strong initiative for the pawn.}) 15... Bd7 $2 ({
As I said before, Black could take on a3.} 15... Qxa3 $1 16. Bc1 (16. g4 Qa2
17. Rc1 Bd7 18. Ng3 {(to stop Nf5 after g4-g5)} Ba4 19. Kd1 Nc6 20. g5 O-O-O
$17 {and there is nothing to attack on the kingside.}) 16... Qa2 17. Rb2 Qa1
18. O-O $44) 16. g4 $2 (16. Bc1 $1 Ba4 17. Kd1 $16) 16... Ba4 $2 (16... Qxa3 $1
) 17. Rb2 {[#] A series of mistakes is over and the logical part of the game
goes on.} Qa6 18. Ng3 {White prepares g4-g5 by preventing Nf5 jump.} Qb7 19. g5
hxg5 $2 ({Black should not allow White bishop coming to g5!} 19... Rh8 $1 20.
gxh6 gxh6 21. Bf4 $16 {White is better, but it is far from the end.}) 20. Bxg5
Qd7 21. Kd2 {[#] Black king is arrested in the center and White pieces slowly
prepare the final assault.} Nf5 22. Qf4 (22. Nxf5 $1 exf5 23. Rg1 $18 {was
also good enough.}) 22... b5 23. Rbb1 Rc8 24. Nxf5 exf5 25. Rbg1 Rh8 26. h6 g6
({or} 26... gxh6 27. Bf6 Rf8 28. Qxh6 $18 {and Qxf8 appears a strong threat.})
27. h7 Qc6 28. Bf6 Kd7 29. Qh6 1-0

