{[#] Black has two extra pawns and his position looks ok. But when there is a
B on d6 a tactic can arise practically at any moment.} 21. Nf5 $1 Rxh4 ({
A queen sacrifice does not leave many saving chances.} 21... exf5 22. Rxc4 Rxc4
23. Qe3 {and Qa7.}) 22. Nxg7+ $1 {White does not take a rook and instead
directs his pieces to the opponent's king.} Kd8 23. Qg5+ f6 $8 24. exf6 {
f6-f7 threat decides the game.} Bxa4 25. f7+ Kd7 26. fxg8=Q Rxg8 27. Qe7+ Kc8 (
27... Kc6 28. Qc7+ Kb5 29. Qxb7#) 28. Qxe6+ Kd8 29. Qxg8+ $18 {with a free
piece and an attack.} *

