{[#]} 27. Bxe7 $1 {The whole article is dedicated to the dark-squared bishop,
but everything has its end. White should correctly evaluate that the Black
knight can become stronger than a bishop (by jumping on d5) and exchange it is
necessary. (You could see such a trick above on move 17 of the Spassky-Uhlmann
game).} ({White is still better in case of} 27. Qxc3 Nd5 {but it will not be
easy to go around Nd5.}) 27... Kxe7 28. Qxc3 $18 {next moves are Rd1, Qb4 (a3)
with a crushing attack against the Black king.} *

