{[#]} 21. R1xd5 $1 {Of course, White could play slowly saving the decisive
advantage, but this combination is the fastest way to end the game.} exd5 22.
Qf6+ Kh7 23. Bxh6 $1 Rg8 (23... Kxh6 24. Qxh8+ Kg5 25. f4+ Kf5 26. Qh3+ Ke4 27.
Qd3#) 24. Qh4 Bg4 {[#] Oldrich Duras missed a chance to end the game even more
beautifully.} 25. Bf8+ $1 ({The game continued with} 25. Nf4 Rh8 26. Nxd5 Qxd6
27. exd6 Bh5 28. Be3 Rad8 29. Qg5 {and Black resigned.}) 25... Bh5 26. Qxh5+
gxh5 27. Rh6# 1-0

