{[#]} 15. Nxf7 $1 Kxf7 16. Qf6+ Kg8 17. Qxg6+ Kf8 {The first moves were easy
to find. Now there is a critical moment of the combination.} 18. e6 $1 ({
Game was continued with} 18. g4 $2 f4 19. g5 Qd8 {and White didn't get the
decisive advantage.}) 18... Bxe6 (18... Be8 19. Bxh6+ Ke7 {Black's last chance
is to give up the rook and to take on c3.} 20. Qg7+ Kd8 (20... Kxe6 21. Kd2 $18
) 21. Bg5+ Kc8 22. Rb1 $1 Qxc3+ 23. Kf1 $18 {and Black loses to a double
attack on b7 and h8.}) 19. Qf6+ $1 $18 {This is the important move that helps
to win the bishop with a check.} *

