{[#]} 24. Bb6 $1 {A modest prophylactic move that practically ends the game.
Black can't stop the appearance of one of the opponent's rooks on the
c7-square.} (24. Rec1 $2 Rec7 {would lose all advantage.}) {The game continued
with} 24... Re8 25. Rec1 Re2 26. Rc7 $1 {White does not care even about the
central pawn.} Rxe4 27. Ng5 Rf4 {and here the Russian GM attacked the rook in
the wrong way} 28. g3 $6 {that made the game unnecessarily longer.} ({It was
stronger to play} 28. Be3 $1 {leaving the h3-pawn defended and moving the
bishop away from the 6-th rank.} Rf6 29. Rac1 Nc5 $8 30. b4 h6 $8 31. bxc5 hxg5
32. cxd6 {(no Bxh3 here and no B on b6 hanging after d6-d7)} Bf5 33. d7 $18) *

