{[#]} 29. Bf3 $1 {Bishop slowly goes to the b1-h7 diagonal. The Q+B battery
will launch a decisive attack.} b5 $2 {A waste of so important time. Black had
to block the diagonal.} (29... Bh4 30. Bd1 Qe7 31. Bc2 f5 32. Rg6 Kh7 33. Rfg1
Raf8 {with the same positions but with a free tempo.}) 30. Bd1 bxc4 31. bxc4
Bh4 32. Bc2 f5 33. Rg6 $1 Kh7 34. Rfg1 Qe7 (34... fxe4 $4 35. Qxe4 $18) 35. Ng3
$2 ({f5xe4 was not a threat. For this reason, White could play a more useful
move instead.} 35. c5 $1 fxe4 (35... dxc5 36. d6 cxd6 37. Nxd6 Rad8 38. Nxf5 $1
$18) 36. Qxe4 Qxe4 37. Bxe4 Nf5 38. Bxf5 Rxg6 39. Rxg6 $18 {with a winning
endgame.}) 35... Bxg3+ $2 {A decisive mistake.} (35... Raf8 {was more
resistible. White is much better, but Black's position strangely remains full
of resources, so it requires some extra efforts for the opponent to break
through.}) 36. Qxg3 Qf7 {Äèàãðàììà [#]} (36... Nh5 {does not give
relief because of} 37. Qf3 $1 Rxg6 38. Bxf5 $18) 37. Bd1 $1 {White wins on the
spot - there is no defense against Rxh6.} Rae8 38. Rxh6+ ({Black resigned
because of such line:} 38. Rxh6+ Kxh6 39. Qg5+ Kh7 40. Qh4+ Nh5 41. Bxh5 $18) *

