31. Rdc1 $1 ({Many of you were trying to find the win after a move} 31. Nc5+ {
(the same as Mr. Milicevic did) but there is nothing after} Kb5 32. Nb3 Ka6 $1
$13 ({the game continued with} 32... Kc4 33. Nd4 Rxf2 34. Kxf2 Nc3 35. Rd2 {
and White managed to transform the material advantage into the whole point.}))
{After 31.Rdc1 Black has nothing good against a threat of Nd3-c5-b3-d4. White
wins the material in all lines.} 31... f6 {Let's see other Black's moves.} (
31... Kb5 32. Rc5+ Ka6 33. Rxd5 $1 Bxd5 34. Nxb4+ $18) (31... Bb7 32. Nc5+ Ka7
33. Nxb7+ Kxb7 34. a6+ Kb8 35. a7+ $18) (31... Ree8 32. Nc5+ Kb5 33. Ne4 $1
Red8 34. a6 Ba8 (34... b3 35. Rc5+ Kb4 36. Be1+ $18 Nc3 37. Bxc3#) 35. Rxc8
Rxc8 36. Nd6+) (31... Re7 32. Rc5 Rb7 33. Rac1 Nc3 34. Nxb4+ $1 Rxb4 35. R5xc3
Kxa5 36. h3 $18 (36. Rxc6 $4 Rxc6 37. Rxc6 Rb1+)) 32. Nc5+ Kb5 (32... Ka7 33.
Ne6+ Ka8 (33... Kb7 34. a6+ Ka8 35. Nd4 $18) 34. Nd4 b3 $1 35. Rab1 $18) 33.
Nb3 $18 *

