{[#] White sacrificed a piece on h6 and now Black needs to decide what to do
with his knight on f4.} 21... Kh7 $1 {Black simply defends on h6 and waits for
gxf4.} ({The game was continued with a natural capture on h3:} 21... Nxh3+ $2
22. Kg2 e4 23. Kxh3 $2 {[#]} (23. Qxh6 $1 {was the correct move order} exf3+
24. Kxh3 {The game would transpose.}) {Black could use a similar idea.} 23...
Kg7 $1 ({Here is the game text.} 23... exf3 $2 24. Qxh6 {Now Giri is safe
thanks to a perpetual check.} Rxe1 25. Qg5+ Kh7 26. Qh4+ Kg7 27. Qg5+ Kh7 28.
Qh4+ Kg7 29. Qg5+ Kh7 {Agreed.}) 24. Nh4 d5 $17 {with a better bishop and a
safer king's position. Though, this position is not the same excellent as that
one that arises in the mainline.}) 22. gxf4 e4 $1 {The difference between the
bishops is enormous.} 23. Nh4 (23. Ne5 dxe5 24. fxe5 Bxe5 25. dxe5 Qxe5 {
is also bad for White.}) 23... d5 $1 $19 {[#] What a position!} *

