{[#] I didn't recognize a scenario of a bad (for Black) middlegame with the
opposite-colored bishops on the board.} 23. Nxe6 $1 {It is equally good to
begin with a capture on d6.} fxe6 24. Bxd6 $1 Qxd6 ({In the game, I was so
scared that decided to give up a pawn right away.} 24... Bxd6 $2 25. c4 Kh8 26.
cxd5 e5 27. Rbb1 $18 {The engine instead hard defends the d-pawn.}) 25. c4 $1
d4 26. Rd1 Bf6 27. a5 {White is much better; his bishop is more perspective;
the d4, b6 pawns require a lot of care; the king side pawn structure is
corrupted.} *

