{[#]} 26... Bxb3 $1 27. cxb3 ({White's only chance is to keep the a-file
blocked.} 27. axb3 a4 {leads to a checkmate faster.}) 27... a4 28. Bc4 axb3 29.
Bxb3 {White's position does not look hopeless, but the next move leaves her no
hopes.} Rxa2 $3 ({White easily defends in case of} 29... Ra3 30. Qd3 Rxb3+ 31.
axb3 Ra8 32. Qxd6+ $18) 30. Bxa2 (30. Kxa2 Qa5+ 31. Kb1 Qa1+ 32. Kc2 {[#]
Another hard moment to foresee.} Be1+ $1 {The only winning move.} 33. Bc4 (33.
Kd3 Qa6+ $1 34. Ke3 Rc3+ 35. Rd3 Qxd3#) 33... Rxc4+ 34. Kd3 Rd4+ 35. Ke3 Rxd1
$19) 30... b3 $1 {Black needs all dark squares on the queen side empty.} 31.
Bxb3 (31. Ne2 bxa2+ 32. Kxa2 Qc4+ $19) 31... Qa3 32. Kc2 Qb2+ 33. Kd3 {[#]} Ba5
$1 {The only winning move. A threat of Rc3 is created.} 34. Bc4 Rxc4 $1 35. Ne2
(35. Kxc4 Qc2+ 36. Kb5 Qc5+ 37. Ka4 (37. Ka6 Qb6#) 37... Qb4#) 35... Qc2+ 36.
Ke3 Bb6+ {A great combination!} 0-1

